news.title: Embassy Group repays ₹1,748 crore debt
news.para: Embassy Group has successfully repaid ₹1,748 crore in non-convertible debentures, leveraging funds from the WeWork India IPO's offer for sale. This strategic move has significantly reduced group-level debt and lowered its stake in WeWork India to 15%, reinforcing the company's financial stability.

news.title: Land prices spike in Chamarajanagar with improved connectivity, industrial development
news.para: Land prices are soaring around Chamarajanagar city. Improved connectivity and new industries are driving this surge. Delays in site allotment by CUDA are also a factor. Private developers are now filling the gap, attracting investors from neighboring states. Land reforms have further boosted interest in the region. Development in industries, tourism, and agriculture is evident.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to map water infrastructure by mid-November
news.para: Gurugram Municipal Corporation (MCG) has set a November 15 deadline for digital mapping of its entire water infrastructure to address data gaps. This initiative aims to improve water supply tracking, consumption regulation, and revenue recovery by identifying pipeline details and boosting station capacities. The move is part of a broader audit to tackle billing issues and illegal groundwater extraction.

news.title: Tribeca Developers repays ₹200 crore construction finance
news.para: Tribeca Developers has successfully repaid a ₹200 crore construction finance facility from HDFC Capital ahead of schedule for its Mumbai project, The Edge. The company, with a significant presence across India, has delivered over six million sq ft of real estate, achieving sales exceeding ₹4,000 crore in FY25.

news.title: NAREDCO elects Parveen Jain as president, Niranjan Hiranandani as chairman
news.para: Parveen Jain has been elected as the new president of the National Real Estate Development Council (NAREDCO), with Niranjan Hiranandani taking on the role of chairman. Jain emphasized a focus on transparency, policy reforms, and sustainable growth, aiming to foster responsible and inclusive development within the real estate sector.

news.title: Bombay HC sets aside state acquisition of private land under Slum Act
news.para: The Bombay High Court has set aside the state's acquisition of private land in Goregaon East, previously declared a slum. Justices Kulkarni and Sathe emphasized that state officials must apply their minds and record reasons before exercising powers under the Slum Act, upholding private landlords' rights.

news.title: Delhi HC rules out giving more time to vacate Signature View apartments
news.para: The Delhi High Court has turned down a plea from residents of Signature View Apartments who were hoping for a grace period to vacate. The court referenced the Supreme Court's serious remarks regarding the unsafe state of the buildings, stressing the risks involved.

news.title: Government classifies limestone as major mineral, eases mining, sale restrictions
news.para: The government has officially recognized limestone as a vital mineral, allowing leaseholders greater flexibility in how they can use or sell this resource. This strategic change lifts constraints and is anticipated to catalyze business operations, leading to more income and job creation in rural areas.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA issues RFPs to develop apartment complexes, 50-storey tower
news.para: Visakhapatnam Metropolitan Region Development Authority (VMRDA) is directly undertaking residential housing projects after a decade, focusing on middle-income group (MIG) housing in Midhilapuri and Vepagunta. These projects, developed via public-private partnerships, will offer affordable apartments. Additionally, a 50-storey iconic residential tower with premium amenities is planned for Madhurawada.

news.title: Mohali collector rates up by 20%-32%
news.para: Mohali district administration has announced a significant hike in collector rates for residential properties, ranging from 20% to 32%, effective October 23. This revision aims to align property transactions with realistic market values. However, commercial property rates remain unchanged.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth ₹44 crore of ex-VVMC chief in Vasai-Virar illegal construction case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has attached properties worth Rs 71 crore in a money laundering case involving illegal construction in Vasai-Virar. Former Vasai-Virar City Municipal Corporation chief Anil Pawar's properties worth Rs 44 crore were seized. The investigation revealed bribes paid to officials for clearing unauthorized building files.

news.title: Developers urge Maharashtra to ensure hassle-free access to M-Sand
news.para: Builders are asking the Maharashtra government for easier access to manufactured sand, or M-Sand. This comes after a new policy to stop river sand mining was finalized. Developers are ready to use M-Sand, which is made from crushed rocks. They need the government to speed up permissions, build better supply chains, and improve transport, especially to rural areas.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body auctions Chandkheda plot, throws in service road too
news.para: Auda officials made a significant error selling land designated for a service road to a developer. This mistake required a refund of Rs 12.7 crore. The land was auctioned for Rs 166 crore. This is not the first such incident, as a similar issue occurred with Lulu International Shopping Malls Pvt Ltd.

news.title: Noida: Sports City dues over ₹11,000 crore, less than 30% recovered so far
news.para: Noida's Sports City projects, launched over 15 years ago, are marred by a massive Rs 11,642 crore debt owed by developers to the Noida Authority. Despite court orders and investigations, only Rs 319 crore has been recovered, leaving promised sports facilities largely on paper while residential towers proliferate.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM outlines plan for a new urban redevelopment policy that rejuvenates cities
news.para: In a significant move, Uttar Pradesh is rolling out a groundbreaking urban redevelopment strategy. The proposed policy seeks to revitalize urban areas with state-of-the-art infrastructure and essential public services. Central to this initiative is the strategic overhaul of land use paired with incentives for private sector contributions.

news.title: Sunac China says most creditors approve restructuring plan
news.para: Sunac China has successfully garnered approval from most creditors for its offshore debt restructuring strategy, a vital move designed to shore up its financial stability during the ongoing slump in the property market. This ambitious plan addresses nearly $8 billion of the company's overseas debt, with final court endorsement on the horizon.

news.title: SC seeks replies of Centre, SEBI on Sahara firm's plea for nod to sell properties to Adani
news.para: The Supreme Court is examining Sahara India Commercial Corporation Ltd's request to sell 88 prime properties, including Amby Valley, to Adani Properties Private Limited. The court has asked the Centre, SEBI, and other stakeholders to respond by November 17. The amicus curiae will collate details of the properties, noting any disputes.

news.title: SC restores 213 flats of Udaipur-based project after ED proactively helps homebuyers
news.para: Home buyers of Project Royal Rajvilas received relief as the Supreme Court released their flats. The apex court also ended the Enforcement Directorate's challenge to the insolvency process. This decision helps over 200 buyers whose dream homes were stalled for 12 years. The court praised the ED's efforts in securing the buyers' interests.

news.title: CCI okays Vedanta's proposal to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: The Competition Commission of India has officially sanctioned Vedanta's substantial bid for Jaiprakash Associates, an important advancement in the company's insolvency journey. Vedanta's offer of ₹17,000 crore has received initial approval, competing against proposals from notable players such as Jindal Power and Adani Group.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 26-acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Godrej Properties has acquired a 26-acre land parcel near Sarjapur Road in South Bengaluru. The company intends to develop a premium residential project on this site, projecting a revenue potential of ₹1,100 crore. This acquisition highlights the Sarjapur Road corridor's significance as a key growth hub in Bengaluru's real estate market.
